  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Education Opportunities for Women (TTC Chilangoma)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Goal Overview: Educate 60  female primary school teachers for rural areas during 3 years at the TTC Chilangoma in Malawi with the final goal to increase participation of girls in primary school education</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Plan: DAPP hereby invited Humana Holland to  support  60 young women  to be trained  as primary school teachers  and thereby become role models and support the  education of  more girls in primary schools. Throughout the 3 year teacher training female and male student are given equal opportunities and challenges  and at the same time the  female student teachers are encouraged to take up bigger responsibilities and be in the forefront of  tasks.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Summary: Malawi suffers from an acute lack of female teachers, meaning those girls who are able to get to school lack the role models to help encourage them to stay. Development Aid from People to People (DAPP) Malawi has a unique teacher training program which promotes gender equity and women&apos;s empowerment. DAPP does not only  train young people to become qualified  primary school teachers, addressing the urgent need for quality teachers, but the education also provides young women and men with sustainable career training and job placement.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Target Groups: 60 young women from poor rural backgrounds</narrative>
  </description>
